        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Over the last few years, Toi et Moi rings have become one of the most talked-about engagement ring styles. While the design itself has existed for centuries, celebrity engagements have brought this romantic ring style back into the spotlight.</p><p>A Toi et Moi ring features two stones set side by side, representing two individuals coming together. The name comes from French and literally means “You and Me.” The symbolism is simple but powerful, which is one reason why many couples today are choosing this design.</p><p>The trend gained momentum when several celebrities were seen wearing unique Toi et Moi engagement rings. These rings often combine two different diamond shapes or even mix gemstones with diamonds.</p><p>At Lucira Jewelry, modern designs like the Pear & Radiant Cut Diamond Toi et Moi Ring, Marquise & Round Toi et Moi Ring, and Emerald & Round Cut Diamond Toi et Moi Ring reflect this same idea of two stones creating one harmonious design.</p><p>Let’s take a look at some celebrity rings that helped bring the Toi et Moi style back into the spotlight.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qw7HLy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Ariana Grande’s Diamond and Pearl Toi et Moi Ring",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Ariana Grande’s Diamond and Pearl Toi et Moi Ring</h2>",
            "custom_id": "ariana",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_A8fUE6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Rich Text ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>One of the most widely discussed Toi et Moi rings in recent years belonged to Ariana Grande. Her engagement ring featured a diamond paired with a pearl, creating a striking contrast.</p><p>The design stood out because the stones were very different from each other. The diamond represented timeless elegance, while the pearl added a softer, more personal touch.</p><p>This combination showed how a Toi et Moi ring doesn’t have to follow strict rules. Mixing stones can create something unique and meaningful.</p><p>Today, similar ideas can be seen in rings like Lucira’s Diamond & Gemstone Toi et Moi Ring, where different stones come together to create a distinctive look.</p>",
            "custom_id": "color",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
